        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23707",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is how I fixed it on our projects - should be extended to look also for other version control system folders...\n\nCheers,\nThomas Gelf\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-26T01:47:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-26T01:47:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23708",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "NB: Adding a filter to ignore directories starting with \".\" (dot) would also be a solution.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-26T01:50:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-26T01:50:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23722",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Not a bug but a feature request",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-26T08:04:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-26T08:04:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23745",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ack. However, even if it is not really a bug: it's a mess for who is using SVN or any similar VCS. And as every developer should do so...\n\n...I consider it at least a misbehaviour :-p",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-26T23:45:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-26T23:45:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23746",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Also not really a misbehaviour.\nAll found files are integrated... if you are using SVN at your customer (never heard of such) you should simply not use directory search.\n\nYou could add the wished files manually.\nAnd you could also add svn ignore to the translation files so they will not be svned and store the original ones in another location.\n\nBtw: Making Zend_Translate dependent of preg* is really bad behaviour.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-26T23:58:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-26T23:58:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23751",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Using SVN (= Subversion) at my customer: I don't get the point?! Our developers have these issues on their development servers. There are no .svn folders on our productional systems.\n\nAnd: they are developers doing their job, writing code as ZF's manual is showing them. They don't care about such issues. The only thing they are aware of is that it \"sometimes\" occurs that new translations \/ changes of character encodings etc are not visible... And they are unable to understand, WHY this is happening.\n\nAdding wished files manually: I know. And I'm doing so. And I'm using nothing but gettext for my translations. I care about performance, I try to avoid useless stat()-calls etc. Unfortunately most PHP developers are NOT doing so. But feel free to teach every coder out there it's job, instead of adding a smart quick fix. It will surely be a better world thereafter!\n\nZend_Translate dependent of preg_*: great point. We should also fix Zend_Locale, Zend_Data, Zend_Db and many others to avoid this seldom-used bad function. But your're right, feel free to use substr() - it's also faster. Ignoring hidden files \/ folders (^\\.) shouldn't break anything and would resolve this issue.\n\nBest regards,\nThomas",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-27T00:36:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-27T00:36:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23769",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "New option \"ignore\" can be used to fix this behaviour.\nDefault it ignores files\/directories beginning with '.'\n\nCan be used to ignore other types like 'tmp' etc.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-27T11:31:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-27T11:31:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23786",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That's great, thanks a lot!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
